Prompt: How do I schedule a workorder?
Answer:
```html Work Order Scheduling Instructions

How to Schedule a Work Order

  • Schedule unscheduled work orders
    1. Select Work > WO Planning > WO Scheduling.
    2. Select Unscheduled WOs for Dataspy in the Activities section of the form.
    3. Select a work order from the list and drag it to the day on the calendar for which to schedule it.
    4. The system creates a new work order schedule record.

  • Schedule backlogged work orders
    1. Select Work > WO Planning > WO Scheduling.
    2. Select Backlogged WOs for Dataspy in the Activities section of the form.
    3. Select a work order from the list and drag it to the day on the calendar for which to schedule it.
    4. The system creates a new work order schedule record.
```

Prompt: How do I schedule a workorder?
Answer:
```html How to Schedule a Work Order

Scheduling a Work Order

  • Function: Schedule unscheduled work orders
  • Procedure:
    1. Select Unscheduled WOs for Dataspy in the Activities section of the form.
    2. Select a work order from the list.
    3. Drag the selected work order to the day on the calendar for which to schedule it.
    4. The system will create a new work order schedule record.

  • Function: Schedule backlogged work orders
  • Procedure:
    1. Select Backlogged WOs for Dataspy in the Activities section of the form.
    2. Select a work order from the list.
    3. Drag the selected work order to the day on the calendar for which to schedule it.
    4. The system will create a new work order schedule record.

Changing Work Order Status

To change work order status:

  1. Select Work > WO Planning > WO Scheduling.
  2. Select a work order and a daily schedule record for which to change the status.
  3. Click Actions > Change WO Status.
  4. Specify the New Status you wish to set for the work order.
  5. Click Submit.
```
